### Issue 1: ARM7 Cycle Accounting in NDS Mode (Critical)

The most critical issue is in `runJitNds()` - you're not accumulating ARM7 cycles into the master clock:

```cpp
acc0 += runCpu(core,0,false);  // ARM9: contributes to master clock
runCpu(core,1,false);          // ARM7: runs but doesn't add to acc
```

**Problem**: The ARM7 runs at half the clock rate of ARM9, meaning 1 ARM7 cycle = 2 ARM9 cycles. But you're completely ignoring ARM7's cycle contribution. This causes the scheduler to never fire ARM7-related events (like IPCSYNC), which explains why Rockwrestler gets "Timeout when ARM7 light is red."

**Fix**:
```cpp
void runJitNds(Core& core){
    if(!g_jitLive||!codeBuf){Interpreter::runCoreNds(core);return;}

    uint32_t acc0=0;
    for(int i=0;i<ITERS_NDS;i++){
        acc0 += runCpu(core,0,false);  // ARM9 cycles
        // ARM7 runs at half speed - each ARM7 cycle = 2 ARM9 cycles
        uint32_t arm7Cycles = runCpu(core,1,false);
        acc0 += arm7Cycles * 2;  // Convert ARM7 cycles to ARM9 equivalent
    }

    uint32_t charge=(acc0>FLOOR_CYCLES_NDS)?acc0:FLOOR_CYCLES_NDS;
    tickInline(core,charge);
    logStatus(core);
}
```

### Issue 2: GBA HALT Instruction Handling (Critical)

In the GBA logs, you see `pc0=FFFF0000` which indicates the ARM7 is stuck. Looking at your GBA runner:

