**Problem**: When the CPU executes a HALT instruction, `runCpu` returns 0 (because `interp.halted` is true), and you charge only 1 cycle. This is insufficient - the CPU needs to advance enough cycles to reach the next interrupt event (VBlank). The floor of 1232 cycles should handle this, but the issue is that when halted, you're not properly checking if an interrupt should wake the CPU.

